---
const steps = [
  {
    num: "01",
    title: "Signal public demand",
    body: "Join the coalition with your email and record a non-binding pledge tier—no charge today. When checkout is live, we’ll email a secure link to complete payment if you still choose to give. Together these numbers show museums, donors, and press that Gus belongs in public stewardship—not a private vault.",
  },
  {
    num: "02",
    title: "Organize institutions",
    body: "A $20–30M auction requires a consortium, not a single checkout. We advocate for the same playbook that brought Sue to Chicago's Field Museum: museums, philanthropists, and civic partners coordinating before and after the hammer.",
  },
  {
    num: "03",
    title: "Secure stewardship",
    body: "The goal is permanent access for research and education—whether through a winning consortium bid, a post-auction arrangement, or public pressure that keeps the specimen in trust. Small pledges seed coordination; institutions carry the scale.",
  },
];
---

<section class="how" id="how-it-works" aria-labelledby="how-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 id="how-heading" class="display how__title">How it works</h2>
    <p class="how__lede">
      This is a grassroots stewardship campaign, not a direct purchase button. Your participation helps build the case before
      <strong>14 July 2026</strong>.
    </p>
    <ol class="how__steps">
      {
        steps.map((step) => (
          <li class="how__step card">
            <p class="how__num" aria-hidden="true">{step.num}</p>
            <h3 class="how__step-title">{step.title}</h3>
            <p class="how__step-body">{step.body}</p>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ol>
    <aside class="how__precedent card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Precedent</p>
      <p class="how__precedent-text">
        In 1997, <em>Sue</em> became the first <em>T. rex</em> sold at auction. The Field Museum acquired the skeleton through
        a coalition of donors and institutions—not a lone private collector. Gus deserves the same outcome.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .how {
    padding: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--clay) 30%, transparent);
  }

  .how__title {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.75rem;
  }

  .how__lede {
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
    max-width: 58ch;
    color: var(--clay);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .how__steps {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0.85rem;
  }

  .how__step {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.1rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .how__num {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--bronze);
  }

  .how__step-title {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .how__step-body {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink) 88%, var(--clay));
  }

  .how__precedent {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.35rem;
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--forest) 35%, var(--clay));
  }

  .how__precedent-text {
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: 72ch;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .how__steps {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
